    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A broad term for art, artistry, artisanry, or craft in Nahua culture. This includes traditions of writing, painting, featherworking, metalworking, and stone-cutting viewed by the Nahuas as inherited from the ancient Toltec civilization.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000179/VP-intern</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000096679/León-Portilla, Toltecáyotl, Aspectos De La Cultura Náhuatl (1980)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000096689/Solis Olguín, Art at the Time of the Aztecs, Aztecs (2002)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een brede term voor kunst, kunstbeoefening, handwerk of ambacht in de Nahua-cultuur. Het gaat om tradities van schrijven, schilderen, veerbewerking, metaalbewerking en steengraveren die door de Nahua's zijn overgenomen van de oude Toltec-beschaving.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Um termo amplo para arte, talento artístico, artesanato ou ofício na cultura Nahua. Isso inclui tradições de escrita, pintura, trabalho com penas, metalurgia e lapidação de pedras vistas pelos Nahuas como herdadas da antiga civilização Tolteca.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
